## Track 1 — Renato Souza: Schema + Repository + Migration + Seed

**Escopo:** Toda a camada de dados: modelo Prisma, migracao, repositorio com todas as queries, seed de dev.

### Arquivos que cria/modifica (ownership exclusivo)

```
mundial-erp-api/
├── prisma/
│   └── schema.prisma                          ← ADD: enums + model Notification + relacao User
│   └── seed.ts                                ← ADD: seed 5 notificacoes mockadas
└── src/modules/notifications/
    └── notifications.repository.ts            ← Repository completo
```

### Especificacao funcional

1. **schema.prisma — Enums + Model**
   - Adicionar os 3 enums: `NotificationType`, `NotificationStatus`, `NotificationCategory`
   - Adicionar model `Notification` conforme contrato (secao Contratos Compartilhados)
   - Adicionar relacao no model `User`: `notifications Notification[]`
   - 4 indices nomeados conforme contrato
   - `@@map("notifications")` + `@map("snake_case")` em todas as colunas
   - Campos obrigatorios Bravy: `id (cuid)`, `createdAt`, `updatedAt`, `deletedAt` (soft delete)

2. **Migration**
   - `npx prisma migrate dev --name add-notifications`
   - Gerar client: `npx prisma generate`

3. **seed.ts — 5 notificacoes mockadas**
   - 2x `TASK_OVERDUE` (category PRIMARY, status UNREAD) — createdAt: hoje e ontem
   - 1x `TASK_DUE_SOON` (category PRIMARY, status UNREAD) — createdAt: 3 dias atras
   - 1x `MESSAGE` (category OTHER, status READ) — createdAt: 5 dias atras
   - 1x `SYSTEM` (category OTHER, status CLEARED) — createdAt: 10 dias atras
   - Todas vinculadas ao primeiro usuario do banco

4. **notifications.repository.ts**
   ```typescript
   @Injectable()
   export class NotificationsRepository {
     constructor(private readonly prisma: PrismaService) {}

     // Queries de listagem por view
     async findByView(userId: string, view: InboxView): Promise<Notification[]>
     // Logica de where por view:
     //   all     → status IN (UNREAD, READ), category IN (PRIMARY, OTHER)
     //   primary → status IN (UNREAD, READ), category = PRIMARY
     //   other   → status IN (UNREAD, READ), category = OTHER
     //   later   → status = SNOOZED
     //   cleared → status = CLEARED
     // orderBy: createdAt desc
     // where: deletedAt = null

     // Contagens (uma unica query com groupBy ou 5 counts paralelos)
     async getCounts(userId: string): Promise<NotificationCounts>

     // CRUD unitario
     async findById(id: string): Promise<Notification | null>
     async create(data: Prisma.NotificationCreateInput): Promise<Notification>
     async update(id: string, data: Prisma.NotificationUpdateInput): Promise<Notification>

     // Bulk operations
     async markAllReadByView(userId: string, view: InboxView): Promise<number>
     async clearAllByView(userId: string, view: InboxView): Promise<number>
     async deleteAllCleared(userId: string): Promise<number>
     // deleteAllCleared faz DELETE fisico (nao soft delete) — spec diz "This cannot be undone"

     // Soft delete padrao
     async softDelete(id: string): Promise<Notification>
   }
   ```

### Performance (principio CTO)
- Indices cobrem TODAS as queries: `idx_notifications_user_status_created` para listagem, `idx_notifications_user_category_status` para contagens por categoria, `idx_notifications_user_status` para contagens gerais
- `getCounts` usa `Promise.all` com 5 counts paralelos (mais simples que groupBy com case when)
- `findByView` usa `orderBy: { createdAt: 'desc' }` e aproveita indice composto
- `markAllReadByView` e `clearAllByView` usam `updateMany` (uma unica query, nao loop)
- `deleteAllCleared` usa `deleteMany` (DELETE fisico conforme spec)

### Criterios de aceite
- [ ] Migration roda sem erro (`npx prisma migrate dev`)
- [ ] Prisma generate sem warnings
- [ ] Seed cria 5 notificacoes visiveirs no Prisma Studio
- [ ] Repository: findByView retorna apenas notificacoes da view correta
- [ ] Repository: getCounts retorna contagens corretas por view
- [ ] Repository: bulk ops afetam apenas notificacoes do userId informado
- [ ] Repository: deleteAllCleared faz DELETE fisico (nao soft delete)
- [ ] Todos os campos mapeados com @map("snake_case")
- [ ] Indices nomeados conforme contrato

